\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces Ellipsoidal verification benchmark rendered in 3D. The ellipsoid is clipped along a symmetry plane to expose the interior solution field. Panel\nobreakspace  {}(a) shows the predicted field $u_h$, which peaks at the center and vanishes on the boundary as expected for the quadratic exact solution $u^*=1-\delimiter "026B30D \boldsymbol  {\xi }\delimiter "026B30D ^2$. Panel\nobreakspace  {}(b) shows the absolute error $|u_h-u^*|$, confirming that the operator pullback and the analytic geometric map are implemented correctly (relative $L^2$ error $=2.26\times 10^{-3}$, maximum error $=5.23\times 10^{-3}$).\relax }}{16}{figure.caption.16}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:forward_poisson_ellipsoid}{{5}{16}{Ellipsoidal verification benchmark rendered in 3D. The ellipsoid is clipped along a symmetry plane to expose the interior solution field. Panel~(a) shows the predicted field $u_h$, which peaks at the center and vanishes on the boundary as expected for the quadratic exact solution $u^*=1-\|\boldsymbol {\xi }\|^2$. Panel~(b) shows the absolute error $|u_h-u^*|$, confirming that the operator pullback and the analytic geometric map are implemented correctly (relative $L^2$ error $=2.26\times 10^{-3}$, maximum error $=5.23\times 10^{-3}$).\relax }{figure.caption.16}{}}
