\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {11}{\ignorespaces Displacement field components on the torus at step\nobreakspace  {}100 of the cyclic loading protocol ($n_{\mathrm  {cells}}=10$, $\delta \approx -\genfrac  {}{}{}1{2}{3}\delta _{\qopname  \relax m{max}}$, reverse-loading phase). (a)\nobreakspace  {}$u_x$, (b)\nobreakspace  {}$u_y$, (c)\nobreakspace  {}$u_z$. The opposite $x$-displacement boundary conditions at $\phi \approx 0$ and $\phi \approx \pi $ produce the dominant $u_x$ pattern, while $u_y$ and $u_z$ arise from the curved torus geometry coupling in-plane compression to out-of-plane deformation. All fields are the direct P1 finite-element nodal solution with no postprocessing interpolation.\relax }}{23}{figure.caption.26}\protected@file@percent }
